Running and the older athlete.
 The beneficial effects of regular, aerobic exercise are well documented.
 Regular running fulfills the criteria for such a program.
 Because of the stresses incurred secondary to its impact loading, however, injuries are common.
 The biological changes that accompany aging can lead to a whole gamut of overuse injuries.
 To reduce these stresses, proper preparation, clothing, running shoes, training surfaces, and training techniques are recommended.
